## Core position

> **We are not building “memory” as chat history.**  
> **We are not building “memory” as RAG with branding.**  
> **We are building a memory system that starts with trustworthy episodes, turns them into reusable procedures, consolidates them over time, and later supports future intentions.**

This is the differentiating thesis:

- **episodic memory** = trustworthy experience layer  
- **procedural memory** = reusable skill / routine layer  
- **consolidation** = compression, abstraction, and promotion layer  
- **prospective memory** = future obligations, intentions, and follow-through layer  

That sequencing is strongly aligned with the research direction in episodic-memory systems, procedural skill libraries, and modern agent-memory surveys. :contentReference[oaicite:4]{index=4}

