## 22.4 Prospective / Intention Memory

### Core idea in simple words

Prospective memory is memory for the future:
- follow up later
- do X if Y happens
- remind me when…
- next time, apply this playbook
- keep this intention alive across sessions and environments

### Why we build it last

Because future commitments are only safe when grounded in:
- trustworthy past traces
- reusable validated procedures
- controlled consolidation
- governance and permissions

### Visual: memory ladder

```text
PAST
  │
  ▼
EPISODIC MEMORY
  │
  ▼
PROCEDURAL MEMORY
  │
  ▼
CONSOLIDATION
  │
  ▼
PROSPECTIVE / INTENTION MEMORY
  │
  ▼
FUTURE ACTION
```

### Why this is the real long-term prize

Prospective memory is what turns an agent from “helpful when asked” into “reliably follows through across time.”

That matters most in:
- personal AI
- wearables
- robotics
- research agents
- AI operating systems
- long-running enterprise agents

